    {
      "id": "5fab7cd279bf1d2641f00ea9dad8621749c80ebc",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-12-25 19:55:17.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(7 inline comments)\n\nThis is somehow causing a bunch of test regressions, though I haven't investigated how.  Both Maloo reports show the same 6-7 tests failing, and normally at worst with some intermittent failure only a single test fails.\n\nOne possibility is that one of OCD structures is not being initialized, so the \"min()\" check is returning 0 for the BRW size?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "83df7f7bd2371a581d4a8930d6aff25c608836d4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 275,
        "name": "Sergii Glushchenko",
        "email": "sergii_glushchenko@xyratex.com",
        "username": "deen",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-01-03 17:13:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI think I've tracked down the issue that was leading to LBUG's in ofd and ultimately to 'test failed to respond and timed out' regressions. The problem was in ofd_grant_chunk() where we should properly handle case when exp is NULL.\n\nNow I'm updating the patch according to your comments and will push it for review soon.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "58bd07be9fa80457e287a964825c84da00f235bc",
