      "date": "2013-01-30 06:32:08.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7: Looks good to me, approved\n\nSergii, you are right that 32MB default LOV_DEFAULT_STRIPE_SIZE is probably too large...  I was thinking the default would be based on the cl_max_pages_per_rpc value, but that is a bit more tricky to implement.\n\nSince this patch is not the one actually changing the PTLRPC_MAX_BRW_SIZE, it is not harmful to land this patch as-is.  The default stripe size should be changed in the following patch.\n\nIt probably makes sense to limit this to min(ocd_brw_size) returned from the OSTs or if that is difficult to implement then some fixed value like 1MB might be OK.  Since this value is easily changed at runtime, it probably makes sense to stick with the 1MB default for now.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 7
    },
